495
00:22:42.404 --> 00:22:43.529
Maybe you are psychic.

496
00:22:43.530 --> 00:22:45.406
When do I die? No. don't tell me.

497
00:22:45.407 --> 00:22:48.284
January 14th.
You get trampled at a concert.

498
00:22:48.285 --> 00:22:51.954
What year? What concert? Is it Cher?
Is she touring?

499
00:22:51.955 --> 00:22:53.332
So. here's the thing. Derek.

500
00:22:54.041 --> 00:22:56.460
That vulnerable kid still lives in you.

501
00:22:57.211 --> 00:22:59.170
We call it the shadow self.

502
00:22:59.171 --> 00:23:04.592
So when it comes to Matthew. you think
you're being a good. selfless dad

503
00:23:04.593 --> 00:23:06.219
when you're coddling him.

504
00:23:06.220 --> 00:23:08.972
But you're not worried
about causing him pain.

505
00:23:09.556 --> 00:23:12.100
The person you're worried about hurting
is you.

506
00:23:12.976 --> 00:23:14.353
And that's selfish.

507
00:23:14.937 --> 00:23:15.938
Damn.

508
00:23:17.606 --> 00:23:18.732
Thanks. Paul.

509
00:23:19.316 --> 00:23:20.359
Thank you.

510
00:23:21.568 --> 00:23:23.278
God. I miss this stuff.

511
00:23:23.946 --> 00:23:26.405
- I can see why.
- Beyoncé.

512
00:23:26.406 --> 00:23:28.534
You got trampled at a Beyoncé concert.

513
00:23:29.701 --> 00:23:31.078
I have floor seats?

514
00:23:32.162 --> 00:23:33.956
- Come on in.
- Thank you.

515
00:23:35.749 --> 00:23:37.834
Look. I'm sorry I ran off like that.

516
00:23:37.835 --> 00:23:41.254
I bought you a magnet
from the gift shop to apologize.

517
00:23:41.255 --> 00:23:42.672
It's the one you liked.

518
00:23:42.673 --> 00:23:43.882
Holy shit.

519
00:23:44.550 --> 00:23:49.513
Yeah. it's like the full-size painting.
but then shrunk down to magnet size.

520
00:23:50.264 --> 00:23:52.557
which is what I assume
the artist always wanted.

521
00:23:52.558 --> 00:23:53.559
Right.

522
00:23:55.477 --> 00:23:56.770
No apology necessary.

523
00:23:57.563 --> 00:23:59.314
I probably went a little too hard
this morning.

524
00:24:01.942 --> 00:24:03.693
Gaby's taking Alice to the Sparks game.

525
00:24:03.694 --> 00:24:05.487
Fun.

526
00:24:06.905 --> 00:24:08.030
- Hey. Louis.
- Hey.

527
00:24:08.031 --> 00:24:09.949
Dad. did you steal
my Vitamin C serum again?

528
00:24:09.950 --> 00:24:10.993
Absolutely not.

529
00:24:12.703 --> 00:24:15.455
I did. I have to go hide it.
and then pretend I found it.

530
00:24:21.545 --> 00:24:22.670
So you're a Sparks fan.

531
00:24:22.671 --> 00:24:24.089
Actually. no. I'm a player.

532
00:24:25.132 --> 00:24:26.215
Cool.

533
00:24:26.216 --> 00:24:27.217
Yep.

534
00:24:28.969 --> 00:24:30.345
You can say it.

535
00:24:31.346 --> 00:24:34.683
It's coming off you
like heat from a radiator.

536
00:24:35.767 --> 00:24:36.768
Look. man.

537
00:24:38.353 --> 00:24:39.688
They really care about you.

538
00:24:41.523 --> 00:24:43.358
And I'm trying to be a good person.

539
00:24:44.109 --> 00:24:45.402
I really am.

540
00:24:46.528 --> 00:24:49.197
I've had to listen to Jimmy say.
"How do I help Louis?"

541
00:24:49.198 --> 00:24:52.868
Or Alice say.
"Do you think Louis is gonna be okay?"

542
00:24:53.619 --> 00:24:56.246
And all I wanna say is. "Who gives a shit?

543
00:24:57.372 --> 00:24:58.915
He killed my best friend.

544
00:24:58.916 --> 00:25:00.374
Fuck that guy.

545
00:25:00.375 --> 00:25:02.544
He should be in jail forever."

546
00:25:03.170 --> 00:25:04.379
But you're not.

547
00:25:05.047 --> 00:25:07.090
Why are you still in our lives?

548
00:25:09.009 --> 00:25:10.260
Why are you here?

549
00:25:15.307 --> 00:25:18.936
Tia and I used to take Alice
to Sparks games actually.

550
00:25:21.355 --> 00:25:23.356
We'd do this ridiculous dance

551
00:25:23.357 --> 00:25:25.775
so we can get up on the jumbotron.
and it went like this.

552
00:25:25.776 --> 00:25:28.861
Started with a robot.
and then we did five. six. seven. eight.

553
00:25:28.862 --> 00:25:30.112
That was it.

554
00:25:30.113 --> 00:25:32.573
And we never got on there. obviously.
Too lewd.

555
00:25:32.574 --> 00:25:35.284
But it didn't matter
because it made Alice laugh.

556
00:25:35.285 --> 00:25:39.122
and it made me laugh.
and it made Tia laugh.

557
00:25:43.669 --> 00:25:44.670
Look...

558
00:25:46.421 --> 00:25:48.090
they may have forgiven you.

559
00:25:49.508 --> 00:25:51.009
but I never will.

560
00:25:51.802 --> 00:25:52.803
Ever.

561
00:25:54.805 --> 00:25:56.557
Tia doesn't get to be here

562
00:25:58.016 --> 00:26:01.520
dancing like an idiot and living her life.

563
00:26:02.396 --> 00:26:04.022
Just because of you.

564
00:26:05.315 --> 00:26:08.192
So the fact
that you could be living your life.

565
00:26:08.193 --> 00:26:11.572
and you're choosing not to.
I fucking hate it.

566
00:26:12.197 --> 00:26:13.699
So much.

567
00:26:16.034 --> 00:26:17.870
It's disrespectful to her.

568
00:26:19.580 --> 00:26:21.665
and it's disrespectful to me.

569
00:26:26.128 --> 00:26:28.463
Man. go live your fucking life.

570
00:26:30.465 --> 00:26:31.717
You got it?

571
00:26:35.846 --> 00:26:36.847
Got it.

572
00:26:38.891 --> 00:26:39.892
Good.

573
00:26:47.816 --> 00:26:49.193
Hi.

574
00:26:51.403 --> 00:26:53.279
I don't know if you remember me.

575
00:26:53.280 --> 00:26:54.989
Louis. right?

576
00:26:54.990 --> 00:26:56.991
Yeah. Louis.

577
00:26:56.992 --> 00:26:59.995
You're the last person
that I expected to see.

578
00:27:04.708 --> 00:27:05.958
Second to last.

579
00:27:05.959 --> 00:27:07.126
I'm his ride.

580
00:27:07.127 --> 00:27:08.586
I'll get myself home.

581
00:27:08.587 --> 00:27:09.796
Probably for the best.

582
00:27:15.344 --> 00:27:17.470
Wow. this is... Yeah. very weird.

583
00:27:17.471 --> 00:27:18.888
I know.

584
00:27:18.889 --> 00:27:22.266
I imagined so many times. you know.

585
00:27:22.267 --> 00:27:23.809
what I would do when I saw you.

586
00:27:23.810 --> 00:27:28.023
and sometimes I slapped you.

587
00:27:28.524 --> 00:27:30.150
Sometimes I hugged you.

588
00:27:31.401 --> 00:27:33.986
And now I'm standing in front of you.
and I have no idea

589
00:27:33.987 --> 00:27:36.864
- what to do with my hands.
- This is my fault. I'm so sorry.

590
00:27:36.865 --> 00:27:39.785
- I should have come here so much sooner--
- I decided.

591
00:27:40.869 --> 00:27:41.954
Louis.

592
00:27:42.955 --> 00:27:45.374
I'm so happy to know that you're okay.

593
00:27:48.418 --> 00:27:50.921
I've really missed you.

594
00:27:51.588 --> 00:27:53.089
And there's so much I've wanted to say--

595
00:27:53.090 --> 00:27:55.175
Honey. did you ever get ahold of the--

596
00:27:56.009 --> 00:27:57.177
Baby.

597
00:27:58.387 --> 00:27:59.971
this is Louis.

598
00:27:59.972 --> 00:28:00.973
Yeah.

599
00:28:01.473 --> 00:28:03.225
Hey. man. How are ya?

600
00:28:03.767 --> 00:28:04.893
Casey.

601
00:28:05.811 --> 00:28:07.646
It's good to meet you. man.

602
00:28:08.230 --> 00:28:09.231
Yeah.

603
00:28:12.609 --> 00:28:15.403
Tomorrow you've got a hike
with Jimmy in the morning.

604
00:28:15.404 --> 00:28:17.446
followed by your neurology appointment.

605
00:28:17.447 --> 00:28:20.325
<i>Liz. again.
you don't have to call me with update--</i>

606
00:28:20.826 --> 00:28:23.452
I like hearing you torture people
who aren't me.

607
00:28:23.453 --> 00:28:25.414
I like spending time with you.

608
00:28:26.415 --> 00:28:29.584
You're actually a fun hang. Mom.
Wanna play <i>Gears of War</i>?

609
00:28:29.585 --> 00:28:32.920
I don't know what that is. but so bad.

610
00:28:32.921 --> 00:28:33.922
Hey. buddy.

611
00:28:34.631 --> 00:28:37.593
- You got a second?
- Derek. not now. We're <i>Gears of Waring.</i>

612
00:28:38.260 --> 00:28:40.846
- Now.
- I'll be back.

613
00:28:42.639 --> 00:28:43.640
For strength.

614
00:28:44.725 --> 00:28:45.851
You're good.

615
00:28:47.436 --> 00:28:49.021
Serious face.

616
00:28:50.480 --> 00:28:51.857
What's up. Dad?

617
00:28:53.233 --> 00:28:55.861
Bud. I owe you an apology.

618
00:28:56.445 --> 00:28:58.113
- Accepted.
- Let me finish.

619
00:28:59.615 --> 00:29:00.824
I love you.

620
00:29:01.950 --> 00:29:05.537
And I love you so much. that maybe
I haven't set you up for success.

621
00:29:06.830 --> 00:29:08.748
You're 25.

622
00:29:08.749 --> 00:29:10.959
You have to figure out your life
on your own.

623
00:29:11.960 --> 00:29:13.670
and you are never gonna do that

624
00:29:14.880 --> 00:29:17.131
if I keep getting your footballs
out of trees.

625
00:29:17.132 --> 00:29:18.799
That won't happen again.

626
00:29:18.800 --> 00:29:19.967
It's a metaphor.

627
00:29:19.968 --> 00:29:21.093
What's-a-for?

628
00:29:21.094 --> 00:29:22.304
I'm kicking you out.

629
00:29:23.597 --> 00:29:24.890
Dude. come on.

630
00:29:25.599 --> 00:29:26.682
I've been trying.

631
00:29:26.683 --> 00:29:28.310
I don't think you have.

632
00:29:32.898 --> 00:29:35.317
And I don't think
I would be a very good father

633
00:29:36.610 --> 00:29:38.779
if I let you stay here and not...

634
00:29:40.781 --> 00:29:42.074
really try.

635
00:29:43.951 --> 00:29:45.410
You have until tomorrow.

636
00:29:52.376 --> 00:29:53.585
Did Mom put you up to this?

637
00:29:54.294 --> 00:29:55.378
No.

638
00:29:55.379 --> 00:29:56.880
This one's all me.

639
00:29:57.923 --> 00:29:59.633
Thought you always had my back.

640
00:30:05.347 --> 00:30:07.057
- You good?
- Yeah.

641
00:30:08.559 --> 00:30:09.560
Poof.

642
00:30:10.769 --> 00:30:13.187
- Being the bad cop sucks.
- I know.

643
00:30:13.188 --> 00:30:15.315
You know. one day he's gonna thank you.

644
00:30:17.776 --> 00:30:19.569
Where are you going?

645
00:30:19.570 --> 00:30:21.780
To apologize to Matthew
for how mean you were.

646
00:30:24.700 --> 00:30:26.492
She's with some guy named Casey?

647
00:30:26.493 --> 00:30:28.202
Fuck that ugly asshole.

648
00:30:28.203 --> 00:30:29.662
He was actually really handsome.

649
00:30:29.663 --> 00:30:30.746
And he was nice.

650
00:30:30.747 --> 00:30:32.124
Sounds like a douchebag.

651
00:30:32.624 --> 00:30:35.001
- Paul.
- Most handsome guys are douches.

652
00:30:35.002 --> 00:30:36.377
We can't help it.

653
00:30:36.378 --> 00:30:37.920
Douche twins.

654
00:30:37.921 --> 00:30:39.923
That's my cue to leave.

655
00:30:41.383 --> 00:30:43.509
Hey. who's that British guy again?

656
00:30:43.510 --> 00:30:45.845
He's the driver that killed Jimmy's wife.

657
00:30:45.846 --> 00:30:49.515
Jesus. Paul.
That's a before-the-hike conversation.

658
00:30:49.516 --> 00:30:52.018
I thought he was one of your gym gays.

659
00:30:52.019 --> 00:30:53.187
He's not gay.

660
00:30:53.687 --> 00:30:55.022
He's English.

661
00:30:55.856 --> 00:30:57.149
So how are you doing?

662
00:30:57.858 --> 00:30:59.276
- I'm better.
- Yeah.

663
00:30:59.776 --> 00:31:03.947
You know what. now I know she's okay.
I don't feel stuck anymore.

664
00:31:05.741 --> 00:31:09.369
Listen. I wanna thank you both.

665
00:31:11.246 --> 00:31:13.832
I never could have imagined
you'd be so kind to me.

666
00:31:15.292 --> 00:31:17.503
and I'm still not sure I deserve it.

667
00:31:19.087 --> 00:31:20.171
Wow.

668
00:31:20.172 --> 00:31:21.672
What's with the speech?

669
00:31:21.673 --> 00:31:23.300
I think he's saying goodbye.

670
00:31:24.384 --> 00:31:25.510
Yeah.

671
00:31:25.511 --> 00:31:26.970
What are you gonna do?

672
00:31:27.804 --> 00:31:29.139
I'm gonna get out of here.

673
00:31:30.349 --> 00:31:31.850
Maybe move to San Diego.

674
00:31:32.351 --> 00:31:34.478
Hear they've got a hell of a zoo.
I love a zoo.

675
00:31:36.021 --> 00:31:39.607
Truth is. I think I'm gonna get back
to graphic design.

676
00:31:39.608 --> 00:31:41.984
No. but the world's worst cup of coffee.

677
00:31:41.985 --> 00:31:43.486
I climbed that mountain.

678
00:31:43.487 --> 00:31:44.987
Fair enough.

679
00:31:44.988 --> 00:31:46.072
I'm gonna miss you.

680
00:31:46.073 --> 00:31:47.157
You too.

681
00:31:48.784 --> 00:31:50.661
Hey. you take care.

682
00:31:51.787 --> 00:31:54.498
And now it's your turn. my friend.

683
00:31:56.875 --> 00:31:58.544
Don't leave it too long to call Sofi.

684
00:31:59.878 --> 00:32:00.962
Who's Sofi?

685
00:32:00.963 --> 00:32:02.463
Thanks a lot for that.

686
00:32:02.464 --> 00:32:03.673
You're welcome.

687
00:32:03.674 --> 00:32:05.049
Who's Sofi?

688
00:32:05.050 --> 00:32:06.551
- No one.
- Tell me.

689
00:32:06.552 --> 00:32:07.718
- No.
- Dad?

690
00:32:07.719 --> 00:32:10.514
What did I tell you
about minding your own business?

691
00:32:11.265 --> 00:32:12.516
Sofi.

692
00:32:13.016 --> 00:32:14.017
Sofi.

693
00:32:20.732 --> 00:32:23.861
If you don't mind.
you've had a tough couple of years.

694
00:32:24.611 --> 00:32:26.571
what makes you think you're ready
to get back to work?

695
00:32:26.572 --> 00:32:27.948
I don't know.

696
00:32:29.116 --> 00:32:34.121
I guess I'm hoping that
if I put myself back out there.

697
00:32:35.581 --> 00:32:37.416
maybe good things will happen.

698
00:32:38.625 --> 00:32:40.252
<i>And I think I finally realized.</i>

699
00:32:41.253 --> 00:32:43.463
<i>I have to be the one
to take the first step.</i>

700
00:32:45.340 --> 00:32:46.508
Hey. Marisol.

701
00:32:47.301 --> 00:32:48.844
Yeah. sorry I've been dodging you.

702
00:32:49.887 --> 00:32:50.929
How you been?

703
00:32:51.305 --> 00:33:51.392
